Russian Equity Movers: Nomos, Sberbank Preferred Shares, TMK

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-06-06T15:32:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-06/russian-equity-movers-nomos-sberbank-preferred-shares-tmk.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  was little
changed at 1,633.49 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow. The
dollar-denominated RTS Index rose 0.4 percent to 1,865.64.  The following are among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Nomos Bank (NMOS RX) gained by its most in almost three
weeks, rising 1.8 percent to 963 rubles after the Russian bank
said net income in the first quarter advanced 20 percent to 2.55
billion rubles ($92 million).  OAO Sberbank’s preferred shares (SBERP03 RX) climbed to a
seven-week high after Chief Executive Officer  German Gref  said
June 3 the lender may convert some to common stock. The shares
jumped 2.4 percent to 71.1 rubles, their highest close since
April 15.  Sberbank’s ordinary shares (SBER03 RX) added 0.8 percent to
95.92 rubles.  OAO TMK (TRMK RX),  Russia ’s largest producer of steel pipes
for the oil and gas industry, advanced the most in more than
three weeks, gaining 2.5 percent to 131.32 rubles after first-
quarter earnings beat analyst estimates.  To contact the reporter on this story:
